userStories.notes:
Files:
- plugins/x/src/tools/create-tweet.ts (replace any casts with typed interface)

Context:
Current code in handle() (lines 37-50):
  const data = await graphqlMutation<Record<string, unknown>>('CreateTweet', variables);

  const tweetResult = (data as any)?.data?.create_tweet?.tweet_results?.result as RawTweetResult | undefined;
  if (!tweetResult) {
    const errors = (data as any)?.errors;
    const msg = Array.isArray(errors) ? errors.map((e: any) => e.message).join('; ') : undefined;
    throw ToolError.internal(msg ?? ...);
  }

Fix: Define an interface for the X CreateTweet response:
  interface CreateTweetResponse {
    data?: {
      create_tweet?: {
        tweet_results?: {
          result?: RawTweetResult;
        };
      };
    };
    errors?: Array<{ message: string }>;
  }

Then call: `const data = await graphqlMutation<CreateTweetResponse>('CreateTweet', variables);`

Access paths become type-safe:
  const tweetResult = data.data?.create_tweet?.tweet_results?.result;
  const errors = data.errors;

Constraints:
- RawTweetResult is already defined in tools/schemas.ts — do not redefine it
- graphqlMutation<T> returns T — check x-api.ts to confirm the return type signature
- Do NOT change graphqlMutation's signature
- If any fields in the response are genuinely unknown, use `unknown` not `any`
